3200.name: Black Willow Leaf
3200.description: A leaf obtained by slaying the black willow lurker. Take this to the Blight Treant.

3201.name: Blight Treant Sap
3201.description: The sap of a blight treant. Take this to Arkenia.

3202.name: Arkenia's Letter
3202.description: A letter written by Arkenia. It states that the Initiation Ceremony of the Shillien Circle is complete. Take this to Tetrarch Thifiell.

3203.name: Mark of Glory
3203.description: A mark given to those who have passed the Testimony of Glory. An item for occupational change.

3204.name: Vokian's Order
3204.description: Collect and return with 10 manashen shards, 10 tyrant talons and 10 guardian basilisk fangs.

3205.name: Manashen Shard
3205.description: A shard of the broken manashen. Collect 10 and take them back to Prefect Vokian.

3206.name: Tyrant Talon
3206.description: The talons plucked from a slain Tyrant. Collect 10 and take them back to Prefect Vokian.

3207.name: Guardian Basilisk Fang
3207.description: The fangs of a slain guardian basilisk. Collect 10 and take them back to Prefect Vokian.

3208.name: Vokian's Order
3208.description: Prefect Vokian's orders. The instructions are to go and seek out the Gandi Chief Chianta in the Town of Dion.

3209.name: Necklace of Authority
3209.description: A symbol given to those representing Pa'agrio Lord Kakai.

3210.name: Chianta's 1st Order
3210.description: Orders of Gandi Chief Chianta. The instructions are to go and recover the flame scepter from the lower orc tribes.

3211.name: Scepter of Breka
3211.description: Scepter of flame which can be obtained from a Breka orc chief. Take it along with 4 other tribes' scepters and go see Gandi Chief Chianta.

3212.name: Scepter of Enku
3212.description: The flame scepter received from the Enku orc chief. Take this, along with the remaining 4 scepters, to Gandi Chief Chianta.

3213.name: Scepter of Vuku
3213.description: The flame scepter received from the Vuku orc chief. Take this, along with the remaining 4 scepters, to Gandi Chief Chianta.

3214.name: Scepter of Turek
3214.description: The flame scepter received from the Turek orc chief. Take this, along with the remaining 4 scepters, to Gandi Chief Chianta.

3215.name: Scepter of Tunath
3215.description: The flame scepter received from the Lennunt orc chief. Take this, along with the remaining 4 scepters, to Gandi Chief Chianta.

3216.name: Chianta's 2nd Order
3216.description: Gandi Chief Chianta's orders. The instructions are to come back for further orders after reaching level 38.

3217.name: Chianta's 3rd Order
3217.description: Gandi Chief Chianta's orders. The instructions are to bring back 20 each of Timak and Tamlin orc heads.

3218.name: Tamlin Orc Skull
3218.description: The head of a Tamlin orc cut off after being slain. Collect 20 of these and take them to Gandi Chief Chianta.

3219.name: Timak Orc Head
3219.description: The head of a Timak orc, cut off after being slain. Collect 20 of these and take them to Gandi Chief Chianta.

3220.name: Scepter Box
3220.description: A box containing the 5 flame scepters recovered from the lesser orc tribes. Take this to Seer Tanapi of the Orc Village.

3221.name: Pashika's Head
3221.description: Kill Pashika, son of Voltar, cut his head off and show it to Breka Chief Voltar.

3222.name: Vultus' Head
3222.description: Kill Vultus, son of Voltar, cut his head off and show it to Breka Chief Voltar.

3223.name: Glove of Voltar
3223.description: Glove that was thrown out by Breka Chief Voltar. Slay Pashika and Vultus, sons of Voltar.

3224.name: Enku Overlord Head
3224.description: The head of an Enku overlord, cut off after being slain. Show this to Enku Chief Kepra.

3225.name: Glove of Kepra
3225.description: The glove thrown down by Enku Chief Kepra. Go and slay the Enku overlords.

3226.name: Makum Bugbear Head
3226.description: The head of a Makum bugbear warrior, cut off after being slain. Show this to Turek Chief Burai.

3227.name: Glove of Burai
3227.description: The glove thrown down by Turek Chief Burai. Go and slay the Makum bugbear warriors.

3228.name: Manakia's 1st Letter
3228.description: Letter of Seer Manakia. Take it to Breka orc chief.

3229.name: Manakia's 2nd Letter
3229.description: Seer Manakia's letter. Take this and go to the Enku Orc Chief.

3230.name: Kasman's 1st Letter
3230.description: Prefect Kasman's letter. Take this and go to the Vuku Orc Chief.

3231.name: Kasman's 2nd Letter
3231.description: Prefect Kasman's letter. Take this and go to the Turek Orc Chief.

3232.name: Kasman's 3rd Letter
3232.description: Prefect Kasman's letter. Take this and go to the Lennunt Orc Chief.

3233.name: Driko's Contract
3233.description: Vuku Chief Driko's contract. The contract contains instructions to hunt the marsh stakato drones in the Cruma Marshlands.

3234.name: Stakato Drone Husk
3234.description: The husks of a marsh stakato drone. Collect 30 of these and take them to Vuku Chief Driko.

3235.name: Tanapi's Order
3235.description: Seer Tanapi's orders. Hunt the Ragna Orc Chief and seers and recover the scepter of Tantosc.

3236.name: Scepter of Tantos
3236.description: The flame scepter of the now-perished Tantos tribe. Take this to Seer Tanapi.

3237.name: Ritual Box
3237.description: A box containing the scepters recovered from the Orcs of the Tantos tribe. Take this to Pa'agrio Lord Kakai.

3238.name: Mark of Prosperity
3238.description: A mark given to those who have passed the Testimony of Prosperity. An occupation change related item.

3239.name: 1st Ring of Testimony
3239.description: A ring given to those Dwarves attempting the Testimony of Prosperity. Find the 4 proofs of prosperity.

3240.name: 2nd Ring of Testimony
3240.description: A ring given to those Dwarves attempting the Testimony of Prosperity. Find Maphr's tablet, which contains the ultimate secrets of geometry.

3241.name: Old Account Book
3241.description: Iron Gate Lockirin's account book. The proof of wealth. Take this to Warehouse Keeper Parman of Town of Giran.

3242.name: Blessed Seed
3242.description: A seed containing the blessings of Maphr. The proof of fertile lands. Take this to Warehouse Keeper Parman of Town of Giran.

3243.name: Emily's Recipe
3243.description: A recipe good for childbirth and childbirth recovery. The proof of fertility. Take this to Warehouse Keeper Parman of Town of Giran.

3244.name: Lilith's Elven Wafer
3244.description: Food regarded as the secret to the Elves' longevity. The proof of health. Take this to Warehouse Keeper Parman of Town of Giran.

3245.name: Maphr Tablet Fragment
3245.description: A fragment of Maphr's tablet, which contains the ultimate secrets of geometry. Take this to Warehouse Keeper Parman of Town of Giran.

3246.name: Collection License
3246.description: A license that allows the bearer to collect guild contributions. Seek out those who still owe contributions and collect the funds from them.

3247.name: Lockirin's 1st Notice
3247.description: A notice that guild contributions are due. Take this to Golden Wheel's Spiron.

3248.name: Lockirin's 2nd Notice
3248.description: A notice that guild contributions are due. Take this to Silver Scale's Balanki.

3249.name: Lockirin's 3rd Notice
3249.description: A notice that guild contributions are due. Take this to Bronze Key's Keef.

3250.name: Lockirin's 4th Notice
3250.description: A notice that guild contributions are due. Take this to Filaur of the Gray Pillar.

3251.name: Lockirin's 5th Notice
3251.description: A notice that guild contributions are due. Take this to Black Anvil's Arin.

3252.name: Contribution of Shari
3252.description: Trader Shari's guild contribution. Take this to Golden Wheel's Spiron.

3253.name: Contribution of Mion
3253.description: Trader Mion's guild contribution. Take this to Silver Scale's Balanki.

3254.name: Contribution of Maryse
3254.description: Maryse Redbonnet's guild contribution. Take this to Silver Scale's Balanki.

3255.name: Maryse's Request
3255.description: Note containing Maryse Redbonnet's request that you bring back 10 leather hides for use in crafting items.

3256.name: Contribution of Toma
3256.description: Master Toma's guild contribution. Take this to Black Anvil's Arin.

3257.name: Receipt of Bolter
3257.description: Miner Bolter's contribution receipt. Take this to Black Anvil's Arin to confirm if Miner Bolter has already submitted his contribution.

3258.name: 1st Receipt of Contribution
3258.description: The contribution receipt received from Golden Wheel's Spiron. Collect 5 receipts and take them to Lockirin of the Iron Gate.

3259.name: 2nd Receipt of Contribution
3259.description: The contribution receipt received from Silver Scale's Balanki. Collect 5 receipts and take them to Lockirin of the Iron Gate.

3260.name: 3rd Receipt of Contribution
3260.description: The contribution receipt received from Bronze Key's Keef. Collect 5 receipts and take them to Lockirin of the Iron Gate.

3261.name: 4th Receipt of Contribution
3261.description: A contribution receipt received from Filaur of the Gray Pillar. Collect 5 receipts and take them to Lockirin of the Iron Gate.

3262.name: 5th Receipt of Contribution
3262.description: The contribution receipt received from Black Anvil's Arin. Collect 5 receipts and take them to Lockirin of the Iron Gate.

3263.name: Procuration of Torocco
3263.description: The bearer of this procuration hereby agrees to make contributions on behalf of Torocco. Take this to Bronze Key's Keef.

3264.name: Bright's List
3264.description: A list of ingredients that Guard Bright has written. "20 mandragora petals, 10 bunches of crimson moss"

3265.name: Mandragora Petal
3265.description: The petals of a mandragora flower. Collect 20 of these and take them to Guard Bright.

3266.name: Crimson Moss
3266.description: Crimson Moss obtained from giant red ants. Collect 10 of these and take them to Guard Bright.

3267.name: Mandragora Bouquet
3267.description: A flower bouquet made of mandragora petals and crimson moss. Take this to Emily in the Town of Dion.

3268.name: Parman's Instructions
3268.description: A note containing Warehouse Keeper Parman's instructions. The instructions are to come back after reaching level 38.

3269.name: Parman's Letter
3269.description: Warehouse Keeper Parman's letter. Take this to Maestro Nikola of the Cruma Tower.

3270.name: Clay Dough
3270.description: A piece of clay that Maestro Nikola has given. Use this to make a copy of the keyhole from the titan's box.

3271.name: Pattern of Keyhole
3271.description: The keyhole pattern made from clay dough. Take this to Maestro Nikola.

3272.name: Nikola's List
3272.description: 20 stakato shells, 10 toad lord sacs, 10 spider thorns and 10 D-grade crystals.

3273.name: Stakato Shell
3273.description: The shell of a marsh stakato. A key ingredient in making the titan's key.

3274.name: Toad Lord Sac
3274.description: The Giant Spider's Poison Sac removed from the neck of a toad lord. A key ingredient in making the titan's key.

3275.name: Marsh Spider's Thorn
3275.description: A thorn removed from the shell of a Marsh Spider. A key ingredient in making the Titan's Key.

3276.name: Mark of Champion
3276.description: A mark given to those who have passed the Test of the Champion. An item for occupational change.

3277.name: Ascalon's 1st Letter
3277.description: Veteran Ascalon's letter. Take this to Mason in the Town of Dion.

3278.name: Mason's Letter
3278.description: A letter from Mason to Veteran Ascalon of Town of Giran.

3279.name: Iron Rose Ring
3279.description: A ring given by Mason. The ring is engraved with the symbol of the iron rose. Complete the revenge in place of Mason.

3280.name: Ascalon's 2nd Letter
3280.description: Veteran Ascalon's letter. Take this to Trader Groot of Town of Giran.

3281.name: White Rose Insignia
3281.description: An insignia given by Trader Groot. It was formerly worn by the medics of the iron rose. Aid Trader Groot in his material gathering.

3282.name: Groot's Letter
3282.description: A letter from Trader Groot to Veteran Ascalon in Town of Giran.

3283.name: Ascalon's 3rd Letter
3283.description: Veteran Ascalon's letter. Take this to Captain Mouen of the Town of Oren.

3284.name: Mouen's 1st Order
3284.description: Cut off and bring back the heads of 100 road scavengers or road collectors.

3285.name: Mouen's 2nd Order
3285.description: Destroy the Leto lizardmen and bring back 100 of their fangs.

3286.name: Mouen's Letter
3286.description: A letter from Captain Mouen to Veteran Ascalon of Town of Giran.

3287.name: Harpy's Egg
3287.description: An egg obtained after slaying a harpy. Collect 30 of these and take them to Trader Groot of Town of Giran.

3288.name: Medusa's Venom
3288.description: The venom obtained after slaying a medusa. Collect 30 of these and take them to Trader Groot of Town of Giran.

3289.name: Windsus Bile
3289.description: The bile obtained after slaying a Windsus. Collect 30 of these and take them to Trader Groot of Town of Giran.

3290.name: Bloody Axe Head
3290.description: The head of a Bloody Axe Elite. Collect 10 of these and return to Mason in the Town of Dion.

3291.name: Road Ratman Head
3291.description: The severed head of a road scavenger or road collector. Collect 10 of them and take them to Captain Mouen.

3292.name: Leto Lizardman Fang
3292.description: A fang from a slain Leto lizardman. Collect 10 of these and take them to Captain Mouen.

3293.name: Mark of Sagittarius
3293.description: A mark given to those who have passed the Test of the Sagittarius. An occupation change related item.

3294.name: Bernard's Introduction
3294.description: Take this letter and go to Sagittarius Hamil of the Village of Floran.

3295.name: Hamil's 1st Letter
3295.description: Take this letter and meet with Sir Aron Tanford of the Southern Wastelands.

3296.name: Hamil's 2nd Letter
3296.description: Take this letter and go to Prefect Vokian of Town of Giran.

3297.name: Hamil's 3rd Letter
3297.description: Take this letter and go to Gauen of the Ivory Tower.

3298.name: Hunter's 1st Rune
3298.description: A stone engraved with a hunter's rune. Collect 10 of these and take them to Hamil of the Village of Floran.

3299.name: Hunter's 2nd Rune
3299.description: A rune obtained from Breka orc overlords or Shamans. Collect 10 of these and take them, along with the snake talisman, to Prefect Vokian.
